$interpreted: : Some Days Later...
Tindoiimu: I've heard everything from Jiyanama...
Tindoiimu: So what? You think I'm gonna drop to my knees and thank you? "Oh, you're so brave! Thank you for saving me, big warrior man!"
Jihasaha: (Uhh...)
Tingko: (She's mad...)
Tindoiimu: Jihasaha I can understand, but Tingko!? Why did you get involved!?
Tingko: (Okay Jihasaha, apologize like we talked about...)
Jihasaha: (I know...)
Jihasaha: Princess, I...
Tindoiimu: Save it. I've already decided on your punishments.
Tindoiimu: I order you both to switch jobs.
Jihasaha: ...What? What do you mean?
Tindoiimu: Because of how you've been treating each other.
Tindoiimu: At first I didn't think too much about it, but now... I've realized it's really affecting Jiyanama and me.
Tindoiimu: So I want you two to do each other's jobs for the day. Walk a bit in each other's shoes.
Jihasaha: (What is she talking about!?)
Tingko: (Is this a prank? She can't... prank us... right!?)
Tindoiimu: The look on your faces tells me you've got something to say?
Jihasaha: No! I will accept my punishment!
Tingko: ...Me too...
Tindoiimu: Alright, get to it, then.

Jihasaha: (Since it's an order, I'll do it... 
Wait a second, I don't even live here? What kind of work can Tingko even do!?)
Jihasaha: (No way...!?)
Tingko: Weird, where'd that rabbit run off to?
Jihasaha: She's got to be more careful...
Jihasaha: Good thing that's handled.
Tindoiimu: Doesn't feel good to be worried like that, does it?
Jihasaha: Princess, where did you come from?
Tindoiimu: There's only one road here. I told the qilin guards to wait back by the forest entrance.
Tindoiimu: You haven't answered my question.
Jihasaha: ...No, it doesn't feel good. Is this how you felt while we were gone?
Tindoiimu: Jihasaha, you may serve me... but we're still a team.
Tindoiimu: We have to take care of each other, and consider each other's feelings.
Jihasaha: I will try harder.
Jihasaha: But... I don't think this is the only thing you're upset about, is it?
Tindoiimu: What do you mean?
Jihasaha: If it were, then you wouldn't be punishing Tingko, too.
Tindoiimu: Well, you're here, aren't you? Why don't you go help her?
Jihasaha: She hasn't asked for my help. She's trying it on her own... If I were to help, I would be disrespecting her abilities.
Jihasaha: That's how I've always treated her.
Tindoiimu: Well, what was that just now, then?
Jihasaha: She cares about you, too, princess. I guess it can't hurt to give her a little assistance now and then, behind the scenes.
Tindoiimu: I'm happy that you're learning. I guess you're not so stubborn after all. But aren't you forgetting something?
Jihasaha: What?
Tindoiimu: You're supposed to be doing Tingko's job, today.

Jihasaha: Ugh... what am I even doing? 
Fighting is way easier than this...
Tingko: Hehe, you're hopeless! Here, let me teach you~
